# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# HWAX Portal — routing destinations.   Format:  <system-id>=<URL>
#
# Set a system's URL here → its tile becomes clickable AND nginx adds /<id>/ → that URL.
# Leave it commented → the tile stays "coming_soon".
# The names/logos/descriptions live in systems.yaml; ONLY the destination is here.
#
# After editing:  ./infra/scripts/restart.sh   (or POST /systems/reload as admin)
#
# ── Which URL to use (IMPORTANT when services live on different servers) ──────
# The URL is used TWO ways, and "localhost" means a DIFFERENT machine for each:
#   • tile click → new tab : resolved by the USER'S BROWSER  → localhost = the user's PC
#   • nginx /<id>/ proxy    : resolved by the NGINX server    → localhost = the portal host
# So write whatever address the destination is actually reachable at:
#
#   same server as the portal :  heax-hub=http://localhost:4180
#   another server (by IP)    :  heax-hub=http://10.123.45.67:4180
#   another server (domain)   :  heax-hub=https://heax.sec.samsung.net
#   sub-path on a service     :  ai-data-hub=http://localhost:8001/dashboard/
#
# Tip: for cross-server setups the nginx /<id>/ path is friendliest — users hit ONE portal
# domain and never need to know internal IPs. (Each service must tolerate being served under
# a /<id>/ base path for its own assets/links; otherwise prefer the new-tab/own-domain URL.)
#
# Per-env: dev edits this file; prod uses config/routes.prod.env via ROUTES_PATH. Any single
# line can be overridden by an env var:  SYS_HEAX_HUB_URL=https://heax.sec.samsung.net
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Uncomment + set the port each project's frontend is running on.
# (Live on this host as of 2026-06-06 — verified responding over HTTP.)

heax-hub=http://localhost:4180
ai-data-hub=http://localhost:8001/dashboard/
mx-white-paper=http://localhost:5173
# report-archive=http://localhost:9304        # not running yet
# smart-twin-cluster=http://localhost:9305     # not running yet
